Responsibilities
Ensuring the smooth and efficient overall day-to-day operations of the Front DeskProvide excellent customer service per the standards of the hotel, and assist in situations to ensure customer satisfactionPrepare reports, handle special projects and assignments as required Requirements:Candidate must possess at least a SMU in  Management, Hospitality/Tourism/Hotel Management or equivalent.Required skill(s): Scheduling, ordering supply inventories, Leadership And Managing.Proven effective supervisory skills including cultivating a positive, high performance team.Able to motivate, mentor and performance manage including corrective action to ensurecontinually high standards.Able to work under pressure and stressful situations while handling multiple tasksAttentive to details and have excellent organizational skills.Excellent interpersonal skills with a positive attitude and be guest focused.Solid knowledge of Microsoft Office and general computer applications.Knowledge of OPERA property management system and reservations management software is an asset.Be able to stand for prolonged periods of time.Required language(s): English, JapaneseAt least 1 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.Applicants must be willing to work in Lippo Cikarang.Preferably Supervisor / Coordinators specializing in Hotel Management/Tourism Services or equivalent.3 Full-Time position(s) available.
